{"name": "tempo-api-python-client", "metadata": {"name": "tempo-api-python-client", "version": "0.11.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/stanislavulrych/tempo-api-python-client", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests"], "summary": "Python bindings for Tempo (https://apidocs.tempo.io/)", "upload_time": 1732132462}, "documentation": ["# tempo-api-python-client\n\nPython bindings for Tempo Rest API.\n\nThis is a Tempo API client library to simplify the interaction with Tempo timesheets. The implementation supports Tempo API v3 and v4.\n\nPip release is available: https://pypi.org/project/tempo-api-python-client/\n\nTempo Rest API documentation can be found at https://apidocs.tempo.io/\n\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall current release by pip\n\n```\npip install tempo-api-python-client\n```\n\n\n## Getting Started\n\nYou need an API token for communicating with tempo REST APIs. \n\n### For v3 use\n\n    from tempoapiclient import client_v3\n\n    tempo = client_v3.Tempo(\n        auth_token=\"<your_tempo_api_key>\",\n        )\n\n    worklogs = tempo.get_worklogs(\n        dateFrom=\"2019-11-10\",\n        dateTo=\"2019-11-11\"\n        )\n\n    for i in worklogs:\n        print(i)\n\n### For v4 use\n\n    from tempoapiclient import client_v4\n\n    tempo = client_v4.Tempo(\n        auth_token=\"<your_tempo_api_key>\",\n        )\n\n#### Retrieve Worklogs\n\n    worklogs = tempo.get_worklogs(\n        dateFrom=\"2019-11-10\",\n        dateTo=\"2019-11-11\"\n        )\n\n    for i in worklogs:\n        print(i)\n\nThere are also functions to retrieve `user` and `team`-specific worklogs.\n\n\n#### Create Worklog\n\n    logged_worklog = tempo.create_worklog(\n        accountId=\"<your_jira_account_id>\",\n        issueId=12345,\n        dateFrom=\"2019-11-11\",\n        timeSpentSeconds=3600,\n        description=\"Something\",\n        startTime=\"17:00:00\"\n        attributes=[{_WorkType_: \"Development\"}]\n    )\n\n#### Update Worklog\n\n    logged_worklog = tempo.update_worklog(\n        id=\"<id_of_the_worklog_to_be_updated>\"  # required\n        accountId=\"<your_jira_account_id>\",     # required\n        dateFrom=\"2019-11-11\",                  # required\n        timeSpentSeconds=3600,                  # required\n        description=\"Something\",                # optional\n        startTime=\"17:00:00\"                    # optional\n    )\n\n#### Delete Worklog\n\n    delete_response = tempo.delete_worklog(<worklog_id>)\n\n\n## Code Format\n\n- Flake8: `flake8 --max-line-length=120 tempoapiclient/*`\n\n- Pylint: `pylint --max-line-length=120 tempoapiclient`\n\n\n## Contributing\n\nContribution is welcome. See [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) for more details.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tempoapiclient", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tempoapiclient.rest_client", "documentation": ["coding=utf-8"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "tempoapiclient.rest_client.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "tempoapiclient.rest_client.RestAPIClient", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "tempoapiclient.rest_client.RestAPIClient.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "url", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "auth_token", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verify_ssl", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "proxies", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "advanced_mode", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tempoapiclient.rest_client.RestAPIClient.__enter__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation